      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne, ¶ 9 July 1891. ¶ H. Moors Esqr &amp;c ¶ Acting Undersecretary ¶ Sir....</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">91.07.09</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Henry Moors</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">R91/6482, unit 611, VPRS 3992/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">9 July 1891.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">H. Moors Esqr &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Acting Undersecretary</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In continuance of former correspondence<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M sought permission to continue the employment of G. French Jr in M to A. Deakin, 14 March 1890;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M to T. Wilson, 1 July 1890; M to T. Wilson, 3 September 1890 (in this edition as 90-09-03a); M to G. Langridge, 26 November 1890 and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M to G. Langridge, 24 March 1891.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I have the honor to solicit, that I may be allowed, to retain til the end of this year the temporary services of George French as Messenger of the Gov. Botanist's establishment, under previous arrangement, namely four days each week, daily payment 5/-. Young French is so conversant with the special duties, devolving on him, that it would take a long time, to train any one else for the position, and thus much time will be saved to me, if I could keep him on longer. As the expenditure is so small, and as it is defrayed out of the incidental vote, I hope the hon. the Chief Secretary will grant this favor<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On 15 July,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the Chief Secretary, A. McLean, minuted: 'Continue to end of this year'. Moors forwarded this information to M with the note: 'At the end of the year it is probable that some other arrangement will have to be made'.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M returned the file 'with<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>best thanks for the consideration shown' on 16 July and it was forwarded to the Commissioners of Audit.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir, your obedient servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Gov Botanist.</p>
         </div>
